{
  "doc_id": "18200",
  "text": "Interestingly, C. concisus infection appears to cause milder, more prolonged diarrhea compared to C. jejuni infection, while C. concisus positive patients still present with the same gastrointestinal complaints following acute gastroenteritis as C. jejuni positive patients [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, several studies have shown a high prevalence of C. concisus DNA in mucosal biopsies from patients with inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] and one study showed a possible association between C. concisus infection and microscopic colitis, especially collagenous colitis [CITATION_6] .",
